{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, cling film, ramekins, pastry brush, large bowl, refrigerator","id":"r252879","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-ouIvYVAN3bs\/XZWcgkM2u0I\/AAAAAAAAeas\/GBJEUpOS6j8c3_QDn6qq3V21tfFOGQpMgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0DZFdD4yUXLFGbVR.png","title":"Hazelnut Bavarian","publishedAt":"2017-09-25T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"4 gelatine leaves, titanium strength"},{"content":"100 g hazelnuts, toasted"},{"content":"500 g cream, 35-37 % fat, chilled"},{"content":"6 egg yolks, from medium eggs"},{"content":"120 g caster sugar"},{"content":"1 tsp vanilla bean paste"},{"content":"1 Tbsp water"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6.5 g","fat":"33.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17.3 g","calories":"1629 kJ \/ 388 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place gelatine leaves into a ceramic or glass bowl and cover with cold water. Leave to soak until gelatine leaves have softened and swelled."},{"content":"Place hazelnuts in mixing bowl and chop <b>8 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Without rinsing mixing bowl, <strong>insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place cream in mixing bowl and whip <b>until cream has thickened\/speed 3<b>, watching cream carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid overwhipping (approx. 2-3 minutes). <strong>Remove butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Transfer to a separate bowl, cover with cling film and refrigerate."},{"content":"Without rinsing mixing bowl, <strong>re-insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place egg yolks, caster sugar and vanilla bean paste in mixing bowl then cook <b>9 min\/70°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Squeeze gelatine leaves to remove excess water. Add squeezed gelatine leaves and ¾ of the reserved hazelnuts then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a large bowl. Set remaining ¼ of the hazelnuts aside for garnishing."},{"content":"Fold reserved whipped cream into hazelnut mixture. Lightly brush water or rum into 8 individual ramekins (6-8 cm), then add Bavarian mixture. Cover ramekins with cling film and refrigerate for a at least 6 hours."},{"content":"Once set, remove from fridge and garnish with remaining hazelnuts before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<strong>Chocolate Bavarian:<\/strong> substitute the hazelnuts with <b>100 g<b> chocolate, broken into pieces. Grate chocolate <strong>8 sec\/speed 7<\/strong> in <b>step 1,<b> then proceed as per recipe.","<strong>Vanilla Bavarian:<\/strong> omit the hazelnuts in <b>step 2.<b> Substitute the vanilla paste with 1 whole vanilla bean pod, seeds scraped and proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","6h 25m","8 portions"]}